question: As per the India State of Forest Report 2019, what percent of the total geographical area of Maharashtra is covered under forest?
explanation: As per the India State of Forest Report 2019, 16.50% of the total geographical area of Maharashtra is covered under forest (50,777.56 sq km). Very dense forest covers 2.83%, Moderately dense forest covers 6.69% and Open forest covers 6.98%.
